Happy New Year! Here’s my last painting of 2023. A mix of gouache and watercolor. I hope everyone reading this has a wonderful and blessed 2024!
Another new piece from a couple months ago! I wanted to have some fun with a more graphic style I haven’t used in awhile.

The latest WIP, from rough sketch to values! It’s been perfectly rainy and gloomy here in the PNW and I’m loving every minute of it. You can bet I’ve been drinking extra tea and coffee, which inspired this painting. Working on coloring and rendering now!

Finished up this painting tonight! It took a couple weeks to make this one because life gets busy, but I’m very thankful for the little bits of time that I do have during the day to spend on something that I love. It’s been awhile since I’ve made a painting just for the enjoyment of the process, but this was one of those paintings!
Something from the sketchbook! This was done a few months ago, with grey marker, and black and white colored pencil.
